{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"57b50c5a-ceaa-4fcd-a914-814753b7fd00","content":"No file found in the working directory — I'll explain the conversion directly.\n\n## Converting to Compiled Bindings\n\nAdd `x:DataType` to your `ContentPage` element pointing at your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout>\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font Size: {0}'}\" />\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**Key changes:**\n1. Add an `xmlns:vm` namespace import for your ViewModel's namespace.\n2. Add `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` on the root element (or any ancestor element).\n\n## Catching Binding Errors at Build Time\n\nCompiled bindings are validated by the XAML compiler. To ensure errors surface at build time:\n\n1. **Ensure `<MauiXamlC>` is not disabled** — it's on by default. In your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <!-- This is the default; do NOT set it to false -->\n   <!-- <MauiXamlC>false</MauiXamlC> -->\n   ```\n\n2. **Misspelled or missing properties** (e.g., `{Binding Themee}`) will now produce a **build error** like:\n   ```\n   XC0045: Binding: Property \"Themee\" not found on \"SettingsViewModel\".\n   ```\n\n3. **Type mismatches** (e.g., binding an `int` property to a control expecting `bool`) are also flagged.\n\n4. If you need to opt out for a specific binding (e.g., a dynamic context), use `x:DataType=\"\"` locally to disable compilation for that subtree.\n\nThat's it — the `x:DataType` attribute is the single switch that turns on compile-time validation for all `{Binding}` expressions in its scope.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a25ec318-7e56-449a-ad5b-88fa02e1b5aa","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"There are no files in the directory. The user is asking a general question about how to convert a .NET MAUI page to use compiled bindings. I'll provide the answer directly since there's no existing file to modify.","outputTokens":627,"requestId":"E852:1EDE:2268E0:28D6BB:69F93E2F"},"id":"684bf943-232a-4372-b19c-4f7d1fddfcfb","timestamp":"2026-05-05T00:47:58.126Z","parentId":"74eeb9b0-bc80-4a55-879a-0ff02175a178"}
